description: Micromonas implements a sustained non-photochemical quenching response to phosphate limitation, driven by light harvesting family protein LHCSR. This protein, allows stable growth under P-limitation and increased growth without major LCH adjustment as phosphate becomes more available. Proteomics results show this alga integrates unique strategies to optimize growth under dynamic ocean nutrient conditions.
